.TH SDL_PixelFormat 3type "SDL 3.1.2" "Simple Directmedia Layer" "SDL3 DATATYPES"
.SH NAME
SDL_PixelFormat \- Details about the format of a pixel\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_pixels\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "typedef struct SDL_PixelFormat
.BI "{
.BI "    SDL_PixelFormatEnum format;
.BI "    SDL_Palette *palette;
.BI "    Uint8 bits_per_pixel;
.BI "    Uint8 bytes_per_pixel;
.BI "    Uint8 padding[2];
.BI "    Uint32 Rmask;
.BI "    Uint32 Gmask;
.BI "    Uint32 Bmask;
.BI "    Uint32 Amask;
.BI "    Uint8 Rloss;
.BI "    Uint8 Gloss;
.BI "    Uint8 Bloss;
.BI "    Uint8 Aloss;
.BI "    Uint8 Rshift;
.BI "    Uint8 Gshift;
.BI "    Uint8 Bshift;
.BI "    Uint8 Ashift;
.BI "    int refcount;
.BI "    struct SDL_PixelFormat *next;
.BI "} SDL_PixelFormat;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Generally this is used with 
.BR SDL_Surface
, and covers many
possible configurations, including paletted data and various bit patterns\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This struct is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

